  "name": "TEMA-VIDYA Trend Following Strategy",
  "description": "This algorithm employs a Trend Following strategy utilizing the Triple Exponential Moving Average (TEMA) and Variable Index Dynamic Average (VIDYA) on a 15-minute timeframe. It triggers entries when the TEMA (length 20) crosses above the VIDYA (length 14), indicating a strong upward trend, while considering the Average True Range (ATR) for volatility assessment.",
  "algorithm_type": "TrendFollowing",
  "prompt": "Design an expert-level TrendFollowing trading algorithm in Python that uses the Triple Exponential Moving Average (TEMA) and Variable Index Dynamic Average (VIDYA) applied to closing price on a 15-minute timeframe. Entry occurs when the TEMA (length 20) crosses above the VIDYA (length 14, short/fast smoothing), signaling a strong emerging trend. Only enter if the 15-minute Average True Range (ATR, length 14) is above its 50-bar moving average, indicating heightened volatility. Exit the position if the TEMA crosses below the VIDYA, or if price closes below the TEMA by more than 1.5\u00d7 the current ATR. Include position sizing based on ATR to limit risk per trade to 1% of notional capital.",
